  <prompt>
    Build `FinancialCalculationToolHandler` — a pure-deterministic `IToolHandler`
    implementation per FR-20 that performs formula-based financial calculations.
    Examples: simple interest = principal × rate × time; compound interest = principal ×
    (1 + rate / n)^(n × time); present value; future value; loan amortization payment;
    days-of-interest accrued; pro-rated amounts. Currency-aware (results carry the input
    currency code). NO LLM call. NO Azure OpenAI dependency. Pure C# `decimal` arithmetic.

    Distinct from `FinancialCalculatorHandler` (task 102) which AGGREGATES extracted
    figures (sum/tax/discount/FX). This handler implements FORMULAS taking parameters
    (principal, rate, time, periods).

    Handler registers via auto-discovery per task 100's contract — implements `IToolHandler`;
    `HandlerId = "FinancialCalculationToolHandler"`; lives in
    `Services/Ai/Handlers/FinancialCalculationToolHandler.cs`. Requires `sprk_analysistool`
    row with `sprk_handlerclass = "FinancialCalculationToolHandler"` + `sprk_configuration`
    specifying supported formulas, default rounding mode, decimal precision.

    Configurable behavior per FR-20 acceptance: handler accepts formula name + named
    parameters from playbook input; output is identical for identical input + same config;
    output includes formula name + parameter snapshot for audit trail.

    Tests: contract test + positive cases (each formula with worked-example numbers
    matching known textbook outputs) + error cases (negative principal where forbidden,
    zero periods for compound, unknown formula name) + config-driven test (rounding mode
    changes deterministic output).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with .NET 8 + financial-formula experience. Familiar with simple
    + compound interest formulas, time-value-of-money, amortization, and the `decimal`
    arithmetic discipline.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `FinancialCalculationToolHandler.cs` implemented in `Services/Ai/Handlers/`;
    auto-discovered; `sprk_analysistool` row deployed; unit tests cover positive (each
    supported formula) + error + config-driven cases; ZERO LLM/Azure-OpenAI dependencies;
    all math uses `decimal`; BFF publish-size delta ≤+0.5 MB; `code-review` + `adr-check`
    green.
  </goal>

