  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context. If &gt;70%, run `context-handoff` then `/compact`. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: New BFF handler; formula correctness; Pillar 2 binding; FR-20
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: all 11 steps below including Step 9.5 quality gates
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read TASK-INDEX; confirm 104 is 🔲; dependency 100 complete.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every &lt;inputs&gt; + &lt;knowledge&gt; file. Extract 4-point contract from
      `HandlerRegistrationConventions.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Design Handler Surface">
      Define `HandlerId = "FinancialCalculationToolHandler"`; supported formulas enum
      (SimpleInterest, CompoundInterest, PresentValue, FutureValue, AmortizationPayment,
      DaysAccrued, ProRatedAmount); `ConfigSchema` with formula name + named parameters
      schema + rounding mode + decimal precision. NO `IOpenAiClient` dependency.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Handler">
      Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/FinancialCalculationToolHandler.cs`.
      Each formula a private method taking validated parameters; all `decimal`. Validate
      formula name exists + required parameters present + parameter signs/ranges correct.
      Emit `ToolResult` including formula name, parameter snapshot (parameter NAMES only,
      not values logged per ADR-015), and computed result with currency code.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author Unit Tests">
      Create `FinancialCalculationToolHandlerTests.cs` using `TypedToolHandlerTestFixture`.
      Cover: contract; positive (each formula with textbook-correct worked example —
      e.g., simple interest of $1000 @ 5% for 2 years = $100); error (negative principal,
      zero periods for compound, unknown formula); config-driven (rounding mode swap);
      telemetry (parameter NAMES only in logs).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Seed sprk_analysistool Row">
      Create `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-financial-calculation-row.json` with
      `sprk_handlerclass = "FinancialCalculationToolHandler"`, `sprk_toolcode = "FIN-CALC-FORMULA@v1"`,
      sample `sprk_configuration`, `AvailableInContexts = "Playbook"`. Deploy to Spaarke
      Dev. Capture evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Build + Tests">
      `dotnet build` + `dotnet test --filter "FinancialCalculationToolHandler"`. Both
      pass. Auto-discovery picks up handler.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify BFF Publish-Size Delta">
      `dotnet publish -c Release ...`. Report absolute + diff vs baseline. Target ≤+0.5 MB.
      With this task complete, cumulative Wave 1 delta should be tracked vs ≤+5 MB total
      R6 budget.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through criteria; record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check`. Both MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update status `complete`; TASK-INDEX 104 🔲 → ✅; reset `current-task.md`. Note in
      task-104-deployment-evidence.md that Wave 1 is now complete and Wave 2 (tasks
      105–108) is unblocked.
    </step>
  </steps>

